title: CIA director dispatched to Moscow to warn Russia over troop buildup near Ukraine
description: President Joe Biden dispatched CIA Director Bill Burns to Moscow earlier this week to warn the Kremlin that the US is watching its buildup of troops near Ukraine's border closely, and to attempt to determine what is motivating Russia's actions.

title: Murder trial in killing of Black jogger begins with a nearly all-White jury
description: The trial for the three White men charged in the killing of Black jogger Ahmaud Arbery is set to begin Friday morning, again drawing the nation's attention to the small-town Georgia case in which race has continued to be a central factor.

title: Even Democrats are now admitting 'Defund the Police' was a massive mistake
description: On Tuesday, a proposal to fundamentally restructure the Minneapolis police department in the wake of George Floyd's death in 2020 was soundly defeated, a setback that even many Democrats acknowledged could be laid at the feet of the "defund the police" movement that some within the party embraced last summer.

title: Aaron Rogers confirms he is unvaccinated, says he is 'disappointed' by media
description: Green Bay Packers star quarterback Aaron Rodgers confirmed he is unvaccinated against Covid-19 and is disappointed with the treatment he's been receiving in the media while appearing on The Pat McAfee Show on Friday.

title: Republican Ed Durr will defeat New Jersey's Senate president, CNN projects
description: Republican Ed Durr will defeat Democratic state Sen. Steve Sweeney, the Senate president, in New Jersey's state Senate district 3, CNN projects.

title: Germany in 'very worrying' situation as unvaccinated drive surge in Covid cases
Retiring GOP lawmaker warns Trump will try to steal the next election
description: Retiring Rep. Anthony Gonzalez has a warning for his fellow Republicans: former President Donald Trump will try to steal the next election.

title: 'A great lion with a big heart': Powell's son pays tribute to his dad
description: Michael Powell, son of the first Black US Secretary of State Colin Powell, makes a heartfelt tribute to his father during his funeral service.

title: The Peloton movement may be over. Shares plunge
description: Peloton investors are going to have to take a meditation class (or several) after its latest earnings report that sent its shares plunging by about a third.

title: Russian diplomat found dead on street outside Berlin embassy
description: A Russian diplomat found dead on the sidewalk outside the embassy in Berlin last month is believed by German authorities to have been a secret agent for a Russian intelligence agency, Der Spiegel magazine reported Friday.

title: Thunberg calls climate summit a 'global greenwash festival'
description: Young climate activists have poured into Glasgow and surrounded the site of the COP26 summit to demand action from global leaders, as the focus of the event turns toward the impact of climate change on future generations.

title: Democrats needed wins. They could be on the cusp of exactly that in hours
description: In the wake of jarring election results in several states on Tuesday, the one thing Democrats appeared to agree on was that they needed action in Congress.

title: See Harry Styles help fan come out during concert
description: The British pop star helped fan McKinley McConnell come out to her mom during his concert in Milwaukee after he saw her holding a sign saying "My mom is in section 201. Help me come out."

title: Dirt, danger and big, big air: Welcome to Red Bull Imagination
description: On the border between Kansas and Missouri, on a flat expanse of the Great Plains about 90 miles south of Kansas City, is a dirt bike track so outlandish that it looks like an imaginary world in a PlayStation game.

title: Germany in the grips of a 'very worrying' spike in Covid cases
description:
• Pfizer says its experimental pill reduces risk of hospitalization, death from Covid-19
• Opinion: Long Covid is real. There are ways to protect yourself

title: New Zealand couple accidentally grow a titanic tuber
description: A couple in New Zealand may have grown the world's largest potato without even trying.

title: The 'bullet' plane that could change flying
description: Is it an egg, a blimp or a bullet? Whatever you might want to call the shape of the Otto Celera 500L, it's one that catches the eye. It looks like no other plane out there, and for a good reason: unique aerodynamics.

title: 'We're not perfect but we're freaking trying': Chloé's Gabriela Hearst on making fashion sustainable
description: When Uruguayan fashion designer Gabriela Hearst was announced as the creative director of luxury fashion house Chloé in December last year, those familiar with her work knew it spelled change for the 70-year-old French brand -- especially given the maison's CEO, Riccardo Bellini, had already indicated he was looking to take the label in a new purpose-driven direction.

title: ABBA are back with their first album in 40 years, but is it a Super Trouper or an SOS?
description: Four decades since their last album, Swedish pop legends ABBA are finally back, in one of the most anticipated musical returns in recent years.

title: Jay-Z left Instagram after a day
description: Grand opening, grand closing.

title: 300 million-year-old fossil skeleton in Utah could be the first of its kind
description: An approximately 300 million-year-old fossil skeleton discovered at Canyonlands National Park in Utah could be the first of its kind, researchers say.

title: As the Dead Sea shrinks, Jordan fights to win back tourists
description: On the shoreline of the Dead Sea, Jordanian comedian and national treasure Nabil Sawalha strides chest-deep into the water, with all the confidence of a swan to a lake.

title: Dwayne Johnson, Ryan Reynolds and Gal Gadot go for the green in 'Red Notice'
description: "Red Notice" has the polished feel of something concocted in a lab for maximum social-media attention (Dwayne Johnson! Ryan Reynolds! Gal Gadot!), then pieced together Frankenstein-style from parts of other movies. Yet the net effect is mildly enjoyable, creating a throwback caper film that showcases its stars doing what they do best, or rather for which they're best known.

title: 'Dexter: New Blood' pretty quickly gets back under your skin
description: "Dexter" finished on such a dreary note in 2013 that the first reaction to a planned revival was "Why?" Yet time has helped expunge the bad taste, as the limited series "Dexter: New Blood" infuses new, um, juice into the old serial killer with a code, placing him in a different climate while probing the age-old question of whether it's truly possible to escape the past.

title: Kanye West talks Kim Kardashian in new interview: 'She's still my wife'
description: Kanye West discussed a range of topics -- from Kim Kardashian to his concept of a house -- on a new podcast episode of "Drink Champs."

title: Remains found in park believed to be those of skier missing for nearly 40 years
description: Human remains found in Rocky Mountain National Park in Colorado are believed to belong to a 27-year-old West German man who went missing 38 years ago during a ski trip, authorities said Thursday.

title: How a warning about food supply sparked panic buying in China
description: Few issues are more important to Beijing than food security. For centuries, ruling governments have grappled with the challenges of feeding a large, expanding population. Droughts, floods and famines feature prominently throughout Chinese history — and rebellions launched by starving peasants toppled numerous imperial dynasties.

title: Armed groups join forces in biggest threat yet to embattled Ethiopian leader
Ariana Grande and Cynthia Erivo are set to star in 'Wicked' movie
description: Pop star Ariana Grande and British actress Cynthia Erivo are set to star in Universal's big-screen adaption of the Tony Award-winning musical "Wicked."

title: How new film 'Spencer' kept Kristen Stewart's Diana in focus
description: Pablo Larrain's "Spencer" gives off "The Shining" vibes long before we see two women in matching outfits walking in step down a corridor. The neat Kubrickian symmetry, the oppressive setting, the stifling presence of others, of ritual, of duty -- it's all there in Larrain's imaginary take on Princess Diana's Christmas from hell. Then again, the moment involving two maids is so throwaway it could also be a nothing, a phantom. It wouldn't be the only ghost lurking in the hallways of this film.

title: Medical correspondent talks with Covid-19 survivors about misinformation
description: CNN's Chief Medical Correspondent Dr. Sanjay Gupta talks with survivors of Covid-19 and how the virus can damage your body.

title: Tottenham Hotspur win first match under Conte
description: Antonio Conte got a crash course in what he can expect as Tottenham Hotspur's new manager after the Italian's first game in charge ended in a 3-2 home victory over Vitesse Arnhem in the Europa Conference League on Thursday.

title: Watch preview of tomorrow's Sesame Street town hall on CNN
description: Characters from Sesame Street talk to CNN's Dr. Sanjay Gupta and Erica Hill about the children's Covid-19 vaccine. For more tune into The ABC's of Covid Vaccines: A CNN/Sesame Street Town Hall for Families hosted by CNN's Dr. Sanjay Gupta and Erica Hill along with Sesame Street's Big Bird, Elmo and Friends. Saturday, November 6 at 8:30am ET on CNN.

title: Accusations of cruelty prompt Modern Pentathlon to remove horse riding from competition
description: The International Modern Pentathlon Union (UIPM) has confirmed horse riding will be dropped from the sport after the Paris Olympics in 2024.

title: White House says OPEC and Russia are putting the global recovery at risk
description: The White House has accused OPEC and its allies of putting the global economic recovery at risk by refusing to pump more oil. That sets up a geopolitical showdown that could spark more price swings and prompt the United States to release crude from its strategic reserves.

title: Timeline of the coup: How Trump tried to weaponize the Justice Department to overturn the 2020 election
description: A full year after the 2020 presidential election, new details are still emerging about former President Donald Trump's unprecedented effort to overturn the results.

title: Another Chinese real estate developer is in serious trouble
description: Another Chinese real estate company appears to be at risk of default, escalating fears of further problems in the country's embattled property sector.

title: 'All they've done is carry dead bodies out.' Despair at site of Lagos luxury apartment collapse as families watch rescue effort
description: Families of the victims of Monday's high-rise building collapse in Lagos have accused the Nigerian government of organizing a shambolic rescue effort.

title: Nicaragua's looming election poses two challenges to the rest of the region
description: Nicaragua's upcoming election on November 7 is expected to hold no surprises, after strongman president Daniel Ortega spent most of the year tightening his grip on the country.

title: ﻿Red Bull Imagination: ﻿A motocross rider's dream come true﻿
description: In the Great Plains of Kansas lies a towering playground for thrill-seeking dirt bike riders, home to Tyler Bereman's Red Bull Imagination competition. Taking place on a custom-built course acting as a 'dirt skatepark', 12 of the best motorcross riders compete to land the craziest tricks and most imaginative lines.

title: Chinese journalist imprisoned over Covid reporting in desperate need of medical care, says family
description: Zhang Zhan, a citizen journalist imprisoned for reporting on China's initial Covid-19 outbreak in Wuhan in early 2020, is in desperate need of medical care, according to Human Rights Watch (HRW).

title: How moments after Trump's coup unfolded on the floor
description: A full year after the 2020 presidential election, new details are still emerging about former President Donald Trump's unprecedented effort to overturn the results. A new CNN documentary, "Trumping Democracy: An American Coup," about former President Donald Trump's attempts to subvert the 2020 election, premieres at 9 p.m. ET on Friday, November 5.

title: Lost species appear alive again in 'The Zoo of Extinct Animals'
description: Thought to be extinct, the baiji dolphin no longer swims in the Yangtze River in eastern China -- but now, you could find it swimming in your living room. Along with other extinct animals, it is being brought back to life as an augmented reality experience.

title: Time runs short for committee investigating January 6 insurrection
description: The House probe into the Capitol insurrection is making its most significant strides yet in gaining understanding of Donald Trump's behind-the-scenes maneuvering before and during his coup attempt against American democracy.

title: China's 'hypersonic missile' may be of a different order to Sputnik
description: "Listen now, for the sound that forevermore separates the old from the new."

title: Rudy Giuliani challenged under oath on his election lies
description: CNN obtained exclusive video that shows Trump adviser Rudy Giuliani, attorney Sidney Powell and others being deposed about their election lies.
